## File Structure

```
src/
├── app/          — routes and layouts (Next.js App Router)
├── actions/      — Server Actions by domain (*.actions.ts)
├── components/
│   └── ui/       — shadcn components (never edit directly)
├── lib/          — utilities and library configs
├── hooks/        — custom React hooks (use- prefix)
├── services/     — business logic (*.service.ts)
├── types/        — shared TypeScript definitions (*.types.ts)
└── generated/    — generated code (Prisma Client)
```

## Code Limits
- Files: maximum **300 lines** — if exceeded, split into modules
- Functions: maximum **30 lines** — extract subfunctions with descriptive names
- Components: a single responsibility — if it does too many things, compose

## Pre-Commit Checklist
- [ ] Lint passes without errors
- [ ] TypeScript compiles without errors
- [ ] Relevant tests pass
- [ ] Prisma Client generated (if the schema changed)
- [ ] Build completes without errors (on release branches)
